data.description: Your Colorado mountain cabin awaits... One-level living and 1848 sq ft with no stairs! Perfect for a weekend escape and equipped for year-round living.  Surrounded by 6-acres of pine and aspen forest, the property sits at 9300' and includes the adjacent lots for a buffer of privacy. You may build additional homes on the surrounding lots. Over-sized 2-car garage & 2 sheds protect your vehicles, mountain toys, and tools. Inside, the den features a built-in office perfect for working from home while gazing into the forest. Large primary bedroom is big enough for a king-sized bed and has a walk-in closet. The bonus room off the primary bedroom could be another bedroom, office, or sunroom. The deck is retro-fitted with additional railings to keep your doggos in, and a completely fenced dog run is attached to the house. You will undoubtedly see all kinds of wildlife in this beautiful mountain community where you'll have private access to the San Isabel National Forest only 15 minutes away for hiking, hunting and exploring. Taos, NM is just under 2 hours for skiing and world-class shopping. Fort Garland is 30 minutes away for convenience stores, lodging and dining. Alamosa is an hour away with box stores, hospital, restaurants, hotels, Adams State University, etc. Have a fun-filled weekend at the Great Sand Dunes National Park, fishing in Mountain Home Reservoir, or golfing in La Veta or Lathrop State Park. Or, just a nice time relaxing in the forest!
